SIMPLE: gospelize
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Gospelize
<hw>Gos"pel*ize</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. &
p. p.</pos> <conjf>Gospelized</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb.
n.</pos> <conjf>Gospelizing</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>.]</vmorph>
<ety>[Written also <ets>gospellize</ets>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>To form according to the gospel; <as>as, a command
<ex>gospelized</ex> to us</as>.</def> <rj><au>Milton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To instruct in the gospel; to evangelize; <as>as, to
<ex>gospelize</ex> the savages</as>.</def> <rj><au>Boyle.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Goss</ent>⟦br⟧
